<p>Choose a title for your conversation (Make it descriptive, maybe provocative, but most of all, it should make sense)</p>
<fieldset class="form-group">
  <%= form.label :title %>
  <%= form.text_field :title %>
</fieldset>

<p>Choose an image to go with your conversation (it will look best if you choose one with a 3:2 ratioâ€”wide, not tall)</p>
<fieldset class="form-group">
  <%= form.label :image %>
  <%= form.file_field :image %>
</fieldset>

<p>Enter the city name central to your conversation. We will link it to the nearest Metro area.</p>

<fieldset class="form-group">
  <div class="form-block">
    <%= form.label :metro_region_city, 'Location' %>
    <%= form.text_field :metro_region_city_display_name, :class => "textbox metro_region_city_display_name", :placeholder => "Enter the city name here" %>
    <%= form.hidden_field :metro_region_id, :class => 'metro_region_id' %>
  </div>
</fieldset>

<p>Give us a short description of what you want to accomplish in this conversation. (By "short," we mean about 250 characters, or two sentences.)</p>
<fieldset class="form-group">
  <%= form.label :summary %>
  <%= form.text_area :summary, :rows => 5 %>
</fieldset>

<%= form.hidden_field :zip_code, value: 'ALL' %>

<script type="text/javascript">
  var selected = function(event, ui){
    $('.metro_region_id').val(ui.item.id)
  }
  $( ".metro_region_city_display_name" ).autocomplete({source:'/search/metro_regions/city', select: selected, autoFocus: true});
  
</script>